ion","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A case path from parent action to a case containing child actions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"wrapped","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A reducer that will be invoked with child actions against non-optional child","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"state.","type":"text"}]}]},{"name":"fileID","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The fileID."}]}]},{"name":"filePath","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The filePath."}]}]},{"name":"line","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The line.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"column","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The column."}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A reducer that combines the child reducer with the parent reducer."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, if a parent feature holds onto a piece of optional child state, then it can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"perform its core logic ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"text":" the child’s logic by using the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ifLet"},{"text":" operator:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  struct State {","    var child: Child.State?","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    case child(Child.Action)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core logic for parent feature","    }","    .ifLet(\\.child, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator does a number of things to try to enforce correctness:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features. It runs the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the parent feature to ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" out the child state, in which case the child feature would not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child’s state is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’d"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"out."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Automatically ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":"s out child state when an action is sent for alerts and confirmation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dialogs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Reducer\/ifLet(_:action:destination:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-4ub6q"},{"text":" for a more advanced operator suited","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to navigation.","type":"text"}]}]}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/Effect":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Effect","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect","url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/